Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

The tests break for a reason.

Note that unit tests for ImageController do not use ImageDeserializer, they are testing Controller directly, by manual generation of deserialised request. That manual tests do not contain format version, and thus the tests fail.

You may either fix the tests or modify the code which attempts to fetch format version from the deserialised request to use some meaningful default in case if the format is not supplied.

Also note that tests for ImageDeserializer also has to be modified, as they are currently getting unexpected output.

Please run "tox test_images_resource" before submitting the next patch set to ensure that these tests do not break anymore.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

These 2 tests are failing: 

https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/v2/test_images_resource.py#L2548-L2555

https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/v2/test_images_resource.py#L2483-L2492

You need to add json_schema_version to "change" for those tests to pass.
